Sixteen people were left injured when a taxi overturned on the N4 near Simon Vermooten road in Pretoria on Thursday .According to paramedics there are no people who sustained serious injuries in this accident.ER24 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said that all that have been injured where transported to the nearest hospital for further treatment.&#8220;All injured were stabilised on scene and transported to various hospitals in the area for further medical care&#8221;, said Mathe.Meanwhile exact details to the cause of the accident is unknown and is being investigated by the police.&nbsp;-TNA Reporter